The paper deals with the complexity of Integer Programming, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the path-width of the column-matroid corresponding to the constraint matrix, which is a graph-theoretic parameter. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves lower bounds and algorithms, which are related to theoretical computer science and game theory, respectively, so cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories.
